1
00:01:23,970 --> 00:01:30,430
[A Love Story: Sunshine of My Life]

2
00:01:30,430 --> 00:01:32,900
[Episode 6]

3
00:01:37,430 --> 00:01:40,280
Lu Zhu. Rhythm, rhythm.

4
00:01:40,280 --> 00:01:43,650
Rhythm! Do you hear me?

5
00:01:45,070 --> 00:01:48,410
I want you to pay attention to the rhythm, not to use your heels to chisel the floor.

6
00:01:48,410 --> 00:01:50,330
Tell me. What are you learning?

7
00:01:50,330 --> 00:01:51,800
Huh?

8
00:02:01,900 --> 00:02:03,750
Lu Zhu.

9
00:02:04,940 --> 00:02:08,740
What's the matter? Are you upset? Don't cry.

10
00:02:09,270 --> 00:02:11,210
Today, the teacher was a bit harsh.

11
00:02:11,210 --> 00:02:13,940
Let me make an announcement.

12
00:02:15,540 --> 00:02:19,270
The Garment Association will be holding a Chinese-Style

13
00:02:19,270 --> 00:02:20,890
Fashion Designer Competition.

14
00:02:20,890 --> 00:02:22,610
I've already promised the organizer

15
00:02:22,610 --> 00:02:26,100
that I will be providing the models for this competition.

16
00:02:28,180 --> 00:02:32,070
I'm planning to give this opportunity as the reward for this session's test.

17
00:02:32,070 --> 00:02:35,950
I'll be choosing the five best trainees to participate in this competition.

18
00:02:35,950 --> 00:02:38,190
Thank you, Teacher Linda. We will surely work hard.

19
00:02:38,190 --> 00:02:40,200
Thank you, Teacher.

20
00:02:41,420 --> 00:02:42,860
All right. Everyone, go rest.

21
00:02:42,860 --> 00:02:45,350
Goodbye, Teacher.

22
00:02:47,130 --> 00:02:47,970
Let's go.

23
00:02:47,970 --> 00:02:49,730
Mo Fan,

24
00:02:49,730 --> 00:02:53,770
can you stay to practice with me for a bit?

25
00:02:53,770 --> 00:02:55,970
I can't today. Tonight, I have to go sing.

26
00:02:55,970 --> 00:02:59,300
Just for a little while. I'm doing so miserably.

27
00:02:59,300 --> 00:03:02,520
I really can't. If I'm late, the boss will deduct my pay.

28
00:03:02,520 --> 00:03:03,850
I'll pay you, is that okay?

29
00:03:03,850 --> 00:03:06,760
Why would you pay me money?

30
00:03:07,310 --> 00:03:10,050
Miss, I really can't today.

31
00:03:10,050 --> 00:03:12,790
Just practice by yourself, all right? You can do it!

32
00:03:12,790 --> 00:03:15,390
Stay with me.

33
00:03:21,480 --> 00:03:24,540
The weather is really just adding to our miserable circumstances.

34
00:03:24,540 --> 00:03:27,810
Say, what do we do if this doesn't work out?

35
00:03:27,810 --> 00:03:29,460
We have to be patient.

36
00:03:29,460 --> 00:03:32,630
I'm quite patient. I'm just afraid of that

37
00:03:32,630 --> 00:03:34,590
opportunistic Lu Jun.

38
00:03:34,590 --> 00:03:36,600
Say...

39
00:03:36,600 --> 00:03:39,640
What do we do if that Zhu Haitian really

40
00:03:39,640 --> 00:03:42,160
acquires the embroidery workshop?

41
00:03:42,760 --> 00:03:44,920
Many things depend on fate.

42
00:03:44,920 --> 00:03:48,760
Doing business is the same. Let nature takes its own course.

43
00:03:48,760 --> 00:03:51,380
Aren't you worried then?

44
00:03:53,620 --> 00:03:57,120
I'm asking you a question. Why are you not responding?

45
00:03:58,400 --> 00:04:01,670
Wait! I remember that when I wanted to acquire the embroidery workshop,

46
00:04:01,670 --> 00:04:04,060
you were against it. Were you not?

47
00:04:05,090 --> 00:04:07,110
Me?

48
00:04:07,110 --> 00:04:08,440
I don't think so.

49
00:04:08,440 --> 00:04:11,520
Then, who said I was an evil businessman?

50
00:04:11,520 --> 00:04:14,720
Do you know that you ruined my reputation?

51
00:04:14,720 --> 00:04:18,270
I-I-I never said that. Right?

52
00:04:18,270 --> 00:04:22,000
Do you think that I don't have evidence? I have a recording.

53
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:24,280
I've never said that about you, President Tang!

54
00:04:24,280 --> 00:04:26,830
Out of everyone I've met, President Tang is t-the...

55
00:04:26,830 --> 00:04:29,820
the kindest, most handsome, m-most responsible

56
00:04:29,820 --> 00:04:34,240
boss. How can I possibly slander you, right?

57
00:04:35,120 --> 00:04:36,830
Are you serious about what you said?

58
00:04:36,830 --> 00:04:38,420
Very serious.

59
00:04:38,420 --> 00:04:40,220
Okay.

60
00:04:42,070 --> 00:04:46,100
You lied to me! How can you be like this?

61
00:04:48,510 --> 00:04:51,380
What are you laughing at? How are you so easily amused?

62
00:04:51,380 --> 00:04:55,400
It's not that I'm very easily amused, it's that I think you are really hilarious.

63
00:04:56,260 --> 00:04:59,780
Look! You're quite handsome when you smile, aren't you?

64
00:04:59,780 --> 00:05:02,360
Seeing your usually icy appearance—

65
00:05:02,360 --> 00:05:06,260
No need to say the last part. Just the first part is enough.

66
00:05:07,100 --> 00:05:09,720
Fine. I originally wanted to compliment you. Never mind then.

67
00:05:09,720 --> 00:05:10,860
Continue then.

68
00:05:10,860 --> 00:05:11,920
Continue what?

69
00:05:11,920 --> 00:05:13,930
Continue to compliment me.

70
00:05:16,290 --> 00:05:19,920
Actually... it's not really a compliment.

71
00:05:19,920 --> 00:05:24,560
I just think you are different than others.

72
00:05:24,560 --> 00:05:26,790
How so?

73
00:05:27,720 --> 00:05:31,520
Other business people only want to make money.

74
00:05:31,520 --> 00:05:34,570
But you... you sincerely

75
00:05:34,570 --> 00:05:37,040
like traditional Chinese culture,

76
00:05:37,040 --> 00:05:40,740
and are actually doing things for the embroidery workshop.

77
00:05:40,740 --> 00:05:43,800
With regards to what you have done for my master,

78
00:05:44,400 --> 00:05:46,780
I'm quite touched.

79
00:05:48,780 --> 00:05:53,040
Do you think I'm a good person because I'm nice to your master

80
00:05:53,040 --> 00:05:55,730
or do you think I'm a good person

81
00:05:56,560 --> 00:05:58,960
because I'm inherently good?

82
00:06:02,080 --> 00:06:04,790
I want to hear the truth.

83
00:06:05,510 --> 00:06:09,380
Just like how I wouldn't say that Mo Fei is a girl who is

84
00:06:09,380 --> 00:06:12,160
skilled at embroidery.

85
00:06:12,160 --> 00:06:14,570
However, in my heart,

86
00:06:14,570 --> 00:06:17,220
you're a very special girl.

87
00:06:23,630 --> 00:06:26,060
I think...

88
00:06:27,610 --> 00:06:29,890
you are an inherently good person.

89
00:06:31,400 --> 00:06:36,660
♫ The sun points to the direction ♫

90
00:06:37,600 --> 00:06:41,450
♫ Where you're at ♫

91
00:06:41,450 --> 00:06:45,250
♫ will instantly become sunny ♫

92
00:06:46,700 --> 00:06:52,190
♫ That day, you said some words ♫

93
00:06:53,050 --> 00:06:56,730
♫ Her smile ♫

94
00:06:56,730 --> 00:07:01,290
♫ is like the glow in the sky during sunset ♫

95
00:07:03,020 --> 00:07:05,590
The rain is going to stop soon.

96
00:07:08,930 --> 00:07:13,780
The blue color of a clear sky only happens

97
00:07:13,780 --> 00:07:15,890
after a rain.

98
00:07:16,620 --> 00:07:24,030
♫ My heart, just this one is for you ♫

99
00:07:24,030 --> 00:07:30,500
♫ Protect me, hold me in the palm of your hand ♫

100
00:07:31,600 --> 00:07:35,090
♫ Your smile ♫

101
00:07:37,130 --> 00:07:39,030
Let me tell you a story.

102
00:07:39,030 --> 00:07:40,550
Okay.

103
00:07:40,550 --> 00:07:45,260
I heard that 800 years ago, Emperor Huizong of Song had a dream.

104
00:07:45,260 --> 00:07:47,710
He dreamed of this color

105
00:07:47,710 --> 00:07:50,480
and really liked it.

106
00:07:50,480 --> 00:07:52,990
After he woke up,

107
00:07:52,990 --> 00:07:56,420
he gave an imperial edict to the porcelain makers.

108
00:07:56,420 --> 00:08:00,200
“After the rain, the clouds disappear and the sky becomes clear."
 (A quote by Emperor Huizong)

109
00:08:00,200 --> 00:08:02,810
"This color is the future."
 (A quote by Emperor Huizong that makes an analogy between the clear blue skies after rain to the future of the empire he ruled)

110
00:08:02,810 --> 00:08:06,060
♫ Your look of happiness  ♫

111
00:08:06,060 --> 00:08:10,330
♫ is my sun ♫

112
00:08:10,330 --> 00:08:17,550
♫ Holding your hand, walking to the end of time  ♫

113
00:08:18,190 --> 00:08:25,790
♫ Look at the light shining in the sky, love is like that for now ♫

114
00:08:25,790 --> 00:08:34,410
♫ I'll embrace you tightly ♫

115
00:08:34,410 --> 00:08:37,690
[Model Classroom]

116
00:08:38,960 --> 00:08:42,760
She really hasn't left yet. Does she have to work so hard?

117
00:09:03,900 --> 00:09:06,250
Keep your shoulders steady.

118
00:09:07,230 --> 00:09:10,100
Mo Fan? You scared me to death.

119
00:09:10,100 --> 00:09:14,360
Didn't you go to your part-time job? Why are you back?

120
00:09:14,360 --> 00:09:17,630
I came back to get something so I came to take a look since I was here.

121
00:09:17,630 --> 00:09:19,410
Continue.

122
00:09:21,610 --> 00:09:24,130
Tuck in your chin. Why do you raise it so high?

123
00:09:24,130 --> 00:09:27,650
Keep steady, keep steady. Stop looking at the ground. Stand straighter. That's right.

124
00:09:27,650 --> 00:09:30,160
Hands. Don't move your hands so much. Turn. Don't be choppy with your strides.

125
00:09:30,160 --> 00:09:32,820
Think about how to move. Can you change your pose at the fixed point?

126
00:09:32,820 --> 00:09:34,080
Like this. Or like this.

127
00:09:34,080 --> 00:09:35,550
Look. Look.

128
00:09:35,550 --> 00:09:37,960
Let's do one more and then we'll rest.

129
00:09:49,630 --> 00:09:53,400
You actually did not come back to get something.

130
00:09:53,400 --> 00:09:55,710
You came specifically to practice with me, right?

131
00:09:55,710 --> 00:09:58,260
Of course not! I came back to get my shoes.

132
00:09:58,260 --> 00:10:02,020
Come on! At this time, even if that's not true, you should say it is!

133
00:10:02,020 --> 00:10:06,100
I'm already so pitiful. Can't you comfort me a little?

134
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:11,730
All right. Teacher Linda is a bit harsh with her words

135
00:10:11,730 --> 00:10:13,590
but she's doing it for our own good.

136
00:10:13,590 --> 00:10:16,500
But I'm really upset!

137
00:10:17,810 --> 00:10:22,720
Being a model is what I've really wanted to do since I was young.

138
00:10:23,390 --> 00:10:25,100
Oh.

139
00:10:25,100 --> 00:10:28,530
I'm pouring my heart out here and all you have to say is "oh"?

140
00:10:32,430 --> 00:10:35,830
Such a shame you have such good looks, because you don't know how to speak!

141
00:10:35,830 --> 00:10:39,480
You are just like my unlucky cousin, determined to be alone for life.

142
00:10:39,480 --> 00:10:41,240
Isn't President Tang all right?

143
00:10:41,240 --> 00:10:42,980
How is he all right?

144
00:10:42,980 --> 00:10:45,430
He is like a mannequin and is a control freak!

145
00:10:45,430 --> 00:10:49,730
- He does not let me do this or that.
- You seem energetic. Why don't you walk a few more times?

146
00:10:49,730 --> 00:10:52,970
Are you serious? You're scarier than my cousin!

147
00:10:52,970 --> 00:10:56,920
Who says that about their own cousin?

148
00:11:19,590 --> 00:11:21,400
Master Li,

149
00:11:21,400 --> 00:11:24,850
you can frankly tell me about any of your worries.

150
00:11:27,420 --> 00:11:31,680
I'm sorry, President Tang. I've wasted your day again.

151
00:11:31,680 --> 00:11:34,380
This situation is really...

152
00:11:35,340 --> 00:11:37,560
Never mind, let's not talk about it.

153
00:11:39,180 --> 00:11:43,650
Lu Jun has already agreed to Zhu Haitian's terms.

154
00:11:43,650 --> 00:11:48,770
In the future, the embroidery workshop may very well collaborate with Haiyao.

155
00:11:51,720 --> 00:11:54,150
Master, don't blame yourself.

156
00:11:54,150 --> 00:11:55,760
He's the one who crossed the line.

157
00:11:55,760 --> 00:11:59,480
It's just... how could he possibly manage the embroidery workshop well?

158
00:11:59,480 --> 00:12:03,350
I also didn't think Lu Jun would go so far with matters.

159
00:12:03,350 --> 00:12:05,280
I'm already old

160
00:12:05,280 --> 00:12:08,570
so it's fine if I have to work hard and experience hardships. My heart just aches for those

161
00:12:08,570 --> 00:12:13,340
hardworking masters who rely on their craftmanship for a living.

162
00:12:13,340 --> 00:12:15,110
But I really cannot do anything.

163
00:12:15,110 --> 00:12:20,130
After all, this embroidery workshop is under Lu Jun's name. In the end,

164
00:12:20,130 --> 00:12:22,570
this embroidery workshop is his.

165
00:12:22,570 --> 00:12:25,250
What I'm worried about now is

166
00:12:25,250 --> 00:12:27,510
that the business passed down by our ancestors

167
00:12:27,510 --> 00:12:29,980
will be ruined by him.

168
00:12:32,050 --> 00:12:34,450
Actually, I have an idea.

169
00:12:34,450 --> 00:12:36,950
I don't know if you trust me or not.

170
00:12:37,820 --> 00:12:41,350
Let me handle Lu Jun and Zhu Haitian.

171
00:12:41,350 --> 00:12:43,930
I hope you and the embroiderers can properly embroider

172
00:12:43,930 --> 00:12:46,430
and create your masterpieces.

173
00:12:46,430 --> 00:12:49,090
In a bit, I want to take you somewhere.

174
00:12:49,090 --> 00:12:52,040
I'll go get my car and wait for you two at the door.

175
00:12:57,740 --> 00:13:03,380
Mo Fei, where is President Tang taking us?

176
00:13:05,410 --> 00:13:08,190
Well, President Tang is someone who keeps his promises.

177
00:13:08,190 --> 00:13:11,340
Since he has already asked the embroiderers to embroider in peace,

178
00:13:11,340 --> 00:13:14,250
then I believe he has already figured out a way.

179
00:13:14,250 --> 00:13:17,060
Whether it is Lu Jun or Zhu Haitian,

180
00:13:17,060 --> 00:13:18,880
he will solve everything.

181
00:13:18,880 --> 00:13:20,660
Are you sure?

182
00:13:20,660 --> 00:13:24,440
Lu Jun, that child, is especially difficult to deal with.

183
00:13:24,440 --> 00:13:29,030
But President Tang is not a character who's easily dealt with either.

184
00:13:29,030 --> 00:13:31,520
Hearing you say that,

185
00:13:31,520 --> 00:13:34,530
it seems like you know President Tang really well.

186
00:13:36,500 --> 00:13:38,680
We just argued a few times,

187
00:13:38,680 --> 00:13:41,510
so I guess I know him quite a bit.

188
00:13:44,480 --> 00:13:48,130
I trust you and President Tang,

189
00:13:48,130 --> 00:13:50,430
but the current situation is really...

190
00:13:50,440 --> 00:13:52,590
Enough, Master. Don't think too much about it.

191
00:13:52,590 --> 00:13:54,960
Let's go take a look first, okay?

192
00:13:57,000 --> 00:14:03,360
[Prosperity Garden]

193
00:14:15,860 --> 00:14:19,920
[Welcome Prosperity]

194
00:14:56,070 --> 00:14:58,780
Master, I say, this place is

195
00:14:58,780 --> 00:15:00,150
much bigger than our current embroidery workshop.

196
00:15:00,150 --> 00:15:02,900
Yes, it is. It's so beautiful.

197
00:15:02,900 --> 00:15:05,030
Also, look, the sunlight here is great.

198
00:15:05,030 --> 00:15:08,320
It is convenient to air dry our embroidery and fabric.

199
00:15:08,320 --> 00:15:11,470
When I chose this place, the most important reason

200
00:15:11,470 --> 00:15:13,920
is that the sunlight is great here.

201
00:15:13,920 --> 00:15:15,810
Also, President Tang told me before that

202
00:15:15,810 --> 00:15:18,450
you can open the doors and windows really wide.

203
00:15:18,450 --> 00:15:21,840
When you embroider, there won't be a color mishap

204
00:15:21,840 --> 00:15:24,590
and it's better for the eyes.

205
00:15:25,300 --> 00:15:28,860
President Tang, you are so thoughtful.

206
00:15:28,860 --> 00:15:31,280
It's Mo Fei who told me about everything.

207
00:15:32,820 --> 00:15:36,330
This place is indeed suitable for an embroidery workshop.

208
00:15:36,330 --> 00:15:40,600
However, I'm afraid I can't afford

209
00:15:40,600 --> 00:15:42,690
such a big area of land in a location like this.

210
00:15:42,690 --> 00:15:45,340
You don't have to worry about that at all.

211
00:15:45,340 --> 00:15:48,590
Because our company has already bought this place.

212
00:15:48,590 --> 00:15:51,750
From now on, you and your embroiderers

213
00:15:51,750 --> 00:15:53,760
can work happily here every day

214
00:15:53,760 --> 00:15:56,390
and do not need to worry about making a living anymore.

215
00:15:57,150 --> 00:15:58,830
Please consider it.

216
00:15:58,830 --> 00:16:01,450
We can open a new embroidery workshop.

217
00:16:01,450 --> 00:16:04,690
How can I open a new embroidery workshop with "two empty hands?"
(No resources)

218
00:16:04,690 --> 00:16:06,960
How can you say you have two empty hands?

219
00:16:06,960 --> 00:16:10,440
Your hands are the resources.

220
00:16:10,440 --> 00:16:13,620
If an embroidery workshop doesn't have you or your embroiderers,

221
00:16:13,620 --> 00:16:16,090
then it's just an empty workshop with signage.

222
00:16:16,090 --> 00:16:18,500
If Lu Jun wants to fool around,

223
00:16:18,500 --> 00:16:20,910
then let him do so himself.

224
00:16:21,760 --> 00:16:24,400
I hope I can continue to collaborate with you.

225
00:16:27,200 --> 00:16:28,920
Please think it over.

226
00:16:43,810 --> 00:16:47,210
Since you've helped me with something so important, how should I thank you?

227
00:16:47,210 --> 00:16:48,950
Well...

228
00:16:48,950 --> 00:16:50,670
What do you think?

229
00:16:51,250 --> 00:16:54,440
When we get back to Shanghai,

230
00:16:54,440 --> 00:16:56,490
I'll treat you to bullfrog.

231
00:16:57,690 --> 00:17:01,800
Then I have to see if I have the time. Let me tell you... I am really busy lately.

232
00:17:01,800 --> 00:17:04,030
Why are you taking my words so seriously?

233
00:17:04,030 --> 00:17:08,440
You! Do you think you are all that?

234
00:17:09,850 --> 00:17:13,980
Are you participating in the Chinese Style Fashion competition?

235
00:17:13,980 --> 00:17:15,880
How did you know?

236
00:17:15,880 --> 00:17:18,480
I've seen the participant list.

237
00:17:19,710 --> 00:17:23,800
Say, I've helped with something so important,

238
00:17:23,800 --> 00:17:29,240
then can you help me with your influence behind the scene?

239
00:17:29,240 --> 00:17:31,650
I can consider it.

240
00:17:32,300 --> 00:17:34,670
- I'm joking.
- So was I.

241
00:17:34,670 --> 00:17:37,850
Wow! You even know how to joke around. So amazing.

242
00:17:37,850 --> 00:17:39,970
There are still many things you don't know about me.

243
00:17:39,970 --> 00:17:43,170
So, do you have confidence in the competition?

244
00:17:43,170 --> 00:17:45,410
Of course, I have confidence!

245
00:17:51,610 --> 00:17:54,630
I have come to this familiar city again,

246
00:17:55,260 --> 00:17:59,590
but which places do we have to go to,

247
00:18:00,470 --> 00:18:04,120
to really be familiar with this city?

248
00:18:07,390 --> 00:18:10,960
As for the people who've appeared in our lives,

249
00:18:10,960 --> 00:18:13,540
what do we do

250
00:18:16,000 --> 00:18:18,870
to truly understand them?

251
00:18:19,580 --> 00:18:23,850
Aren't you going to say thanks for getting a ride in someone else's car?

252
00:18:25,540 --> 00:18:28,940
Don't you need to say thanks to the person guiding you?

253
00:18:28,940 --> 00:18:31,340
I will not give up easily.

254
00:18:32,340 --> 00:18:35,040
I hope you can be like me

255
00:18:35,040 --> 00:18:37,470
and try your very best.

256
00:18:38,270 --> 00:18:39,970
All right?

257
